<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JUN 94 / Finance director jailed for 4 years
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A finance director who stole more than Pounds 350,000 from his company,
causing its collapse with the loss of 200 jobs, was jailed for four years
yesterday.
Mr Richard Oates, 44, took the money to finance a lavish lifestyle. As a
result Bristol-based Godwin Warren Engineering folded in 1988.
Mr Oates, now of Mold, north Wales, was convicted at Bristol Crown Court on
five specimen counts of theft and one of publishing a false statement. He
was acquitted on four charges of false accounting.
His co-defendant Mr Jeremy Kirk, finance director of Data Group, which was
owned by Godwin Warren, was convicted of four charges of false accounting.
Mr Kirk, 37, of Clifton, Bristol was ordered to do 240 hours of community
service.
</TEXT>
