FT  24 JUN 94 / Nationalists lead in Scottish poll
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Scottish National party is narrowly ahead of Labour in Monklands East,
scene of the by-election to choose a successor to John Smith, according to
an opinion poll published by the Scottish Daily Express yesterday.
Defeat on June 30 would be a blow for Labour, but the party dismissed the
poll, saying that the sample size of 401 was too small to be reliable.
