FT  23 JUN 94 / Patten to issue apology in court
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr John Patten, the education secretary, is expected to agree in court today
to pay damages and to apologise unreservedly to Birmingham's chief education
officer whom he called 'a nutter'.
A solicitor for Mr Patten is expected to admit that his remarks about
Professor Tim Brighouse were untrue and without justification.
Mr Patten's comments were made while he was speaking to a fringe meeting at
last October's Tory party conference. He said Birmingham education authority
was useless and had apointed 'this nutter' as director.
He accused Prof Brighouse, chief education officer in Oxfordshire between
1978 and 1989, of 'blathering away about education dreams and visions' and
getting the county's service into a 'dreadful muddle' before he was made
professor of education at Keele University 'as a reward'.
Schools threat, Page 10
