<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / Albanians boycott census
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURA SILBER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BELGRADE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ethnic Albanians yesterday refused to participate in the census in
Macedonia, a move which threatens to heighten tensions in the fragile Balkan
republic. For the second day running, ethnic Albanians ignored the
population survey, which they hope will confirm that their numbers warrant
greater participation in the Macedonian state. They have objected to the
number of documents needed to prove citizenship, which they say most
Albanians do not have. Albanians claim that they account for nearly twice as
much as the official figure of 22 per cent, established in the 1991 census -
which they boycotted. If ethnic Albanians decide to launch a mass boycott,
the Party of Democratic Prosperity, their main political group, is likely
pull out of the coalition government. With elections planned for this year,
an Albanian withdrawal would upset the fragile coexistence with the majority
Slavic Macedonians and undermine stability in the republic itself.
</TEXT>
