<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / Canada
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gold shares lost ground and held back a fledgling recovery in Toronto, the
TSE 300 index closing just 4.6 points better at 4,052.2. The slight increase
in the index followed six straight days of losses.
Overall declines still held an advantage over advances, by 421 to 354.
Volume contracted to 54.1m shares from Tuesday's 64.9m, and trading value
amounted to CDollars 663.4m.
Turnover was boosted by heavy trading in the shares of Falconbridge, which
today completed its initial public offering for proceeds of about CDollars
750m. Falconbridge shares lost CDollars  1/2 at CDollars 17 1/2 .
Ten of the 14 stock groups rose, led by real estate and forestry, which
gained 2.22 and 2.09 per cent respectively.
Carena Developments rose 26 cents to CDollars 1.75 on reporting higher
six-month earnings.
