conditions, writes David Waller in Frankfurt.
The 1-for-10 issue was announced in early May, shortly after the
Bavaria-based bank reported a 33 per cent rise in earnings for last year.
Since then, bank shares have underperformed the DAX index of leading German
shares.
Meanwhile, Daimler-Benz, Germany's biggest industrial company, insisted it
would not pull its DM3bn international offering. This is in spite of a
narrowing of the gap between the price of the new shares and the market
price, from 20 per cent when first announced to 13 per cent yesterday.
