Petron, the country's biggest oil refiner, Reuter reports from Manila.
Mr Delfin Lazaro, Energy Secretary, said: 'It is possible that a single
bidder can acquire all 300m shares.' A further 700m will be sold at a fixed
price of between seven and 11 pesos (US 40 cents).
The government plans to retain 40 per cent of Petron through Philippine
National Oil.
Petron is expected to be listed on the Philippine Stock Exchange by
September.
</TEXT>
