</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM DELLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hardys &amp; Hansons, the Nottingham-based independent brewer, yesterday
reported a 10 per cent increase in interim profits.
On turnover marginally ahead to Pounds 15.6m, trading profits advanced to
Pounds 3.35m (Pounds 2.94m); after reduced net interest receivable of Pounds
292,000 (Pounds 338,000) the pre-tax line for the half year to April 1
amounted to Pounds 3.66m, up from Pounds 3.32m last time.
