<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 94 / Society defends insolvency practice
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Society of Practitioners of Insolvency yesterday defended the practice
by which bankers can appoint as receivers the same firm of accountants they
initially hired to investigate a troubled company.
Critics have said there may be a potential conflict of interest in the
arrangement and have called for an independent inquiry. The society said a
consultation it carried out with the accountancy profession's joint ethics
committee two years ago concluded that the 'overwhelming majority' of those
asked supported the position. But details from the survey submitted to the
Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales last year show that
30 per cent believed there was a conflict.
</TEXT>
